  "texts": [
    "Instead, we consider the possibility that CA3 can store both MF and PP encodings for each memory and retrieve either of them.",
    "Inhibitory tone selects between the two; with a higher activity threshold, sparser MF patterns are more likely to be recovered, and the opposite holds for denser PP patterns.",
    "By encoding the same memory in two different ways, each can be leveraged for a different computational purpose.",
    "Conceptually, in terms of energy landscapes, sparser patterns have narrower attractor basins than denser patterns because fewer neurons actively participate (Fig. 1B).",
    "Moreover, less correlated patterns are located farther apart compared to more correlated patterns."
